# Institute of Digital Risk (IDR) – Landing Page

A modern responsive landing page for the **Institute of Digital Risk (IDR)**.
This project showcases a professional institute website focused on **digital risk, cyber governance, and AI risk education**.

The page is designed with a **dark professional UI**, animated visual elements, and a responsive layout suitable for both desktop and mobile devices.

---

# Project Overview

This landing page represents the concept of an **industry-led training institute** that focuses on developing professionals in the field of digital risk and emerging technology governance.

The design focuses on:

* Modern professional UI
* Clean typography
* Smooth scrolling experience
* Interactive animations
* Mobile responsive layout
* Structured sections for information clarity

---

# Technologies Used

## HTML

The entire page structure was written manually in **HTML**.
All sections including navigation, hero section, services, community, contact form, and footer are structured using semantic HTML.

## CSS

The styling is created using **advanced CSS techniques** including:

* CSS variables
* responsive layouts
* animations
* grid and flexbox
* UI hover interactions

Some parts of the advanced CSS styling were enhanced using assistance from AI tools including:

* Qrepter
* Bolt.new
* Gemini
* ChatGPT
* Cloud AI

However, the **color theme and grid background styling were primarily implemented using Cloud AI assistance and manual adjustments.**

## JavaScript

All **JavaScript functionality was written manually**.

JavaScript is used for:

* mobile navigation toggle
* scroll-based navbar styling
* fade-in animations using Intersection Observer
* smooth scrolling
* contact form interaction and success message display

---

# SVG Assets

The SVG graphics used in the navigation logo and other visual elements were **generated using Gemini AI**.

These SVGs were then integrated manually into the HTML structure.

---

# Icons

The project uses **Font Awesome icons** for UI consistency.

Icons are used for:

* feature highlights
* service cards
* community sections
* contact information
* success messages

Font Awesome CDN is used for loading icons.

---

# Key Features

## Responsive Design

The website is fully responsive and adapts to:

* desktop
* tablets
* mobile devices

## Animated Hero Section

The hero section includes:

* animated 3D cube
* orbit rings
* glowing digital theme
* animated statistics section

## Smooth Scroll Navigation

All navigation links smoothly scroll to their respective sections.

## Interactive Mobile Menu

A hamburger menu appears on smaller screens with animated open/close behavior.

## Scroll Animations

Elements appear using **fade-up animations** triggered by Intersection Observer.

## Contact Form UI

The contact form includes:

* structured input fields
* validation
* success message display

---

# Website Sections

The landing page contains the following sections:

Navigation
Hero Section
About Section
Services / Pillars
Practitioner Pipeline
Community Section
Contact Form
Footer

---

# Design Philosophy

The design follows a **modern digital institute aesthetic**, combining:

* dark professional UI
* orange accent color
* geometric background grid
* structured layout
* subtle animations

The goal was to create a website that feels suitable for:

* technology institutes
* cybersecurity education
* AI governance training
* digital risk advisory organizations

